{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_23","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `jakarta.enterprise:jakarta.enterprise.cdi-api:3.0.0`. Preserved work is available on the branch:\nhttps://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-6215-fails-javac-compile-jakarta.enterprise-jakarta.enterprise.cdi-api-3.0.0-9801867f\n\nThe run did hit the expected `javac` failure first: `SecurityActionsTest.java` imports `javax.enterprise.util.AnnotationLiteral`, which does not exist in CDI `3.0.0`, so `:compileTestJava` fails with `package javax.enterprise.util does not exist` and the follow-on `AnnotationLiteral` symbol errors. See `human-intervention-logs/jakarta.enterprise:jakarta.enterprise.cdi-api:3.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-08T03-15-37-378712Z.log`.\n\nHowever, the preserved branch appears to repair that compile problem: later reruns show `compileTestJava`, `test`, and `nativeTest` succeeding for the generated `SecurityActionsTest`. See `human-intervention-logs/jakarta.enterprise:jakarta.enterprise.cdi-api:3.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-08T03-16-06-071274Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/jakarta.enterprise:jakarta.enterprise.cdi-api:3.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-08T03-20-19-544489Z.log`, and `human-intervention-logs/jakarta.enterprise:jakarta.enterprise.cdi-api:3.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-08T03-22-30-431255Z.log`.\n\nThe most likely stage that still fails is downstream metadata generation. In `human-intervention-logs/jakarta.enterprise:jakarta.enterprise.cdi-api:3.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-06-08T03-21-03-791408Z.log`, `:generateMetadata` fails because the JVM cannot load the native-image agent: `Could not find agent library native-image-agent on the library path, with error: libnative-image-agent.so: cannot open shared object file`. That aborts `:test` during agent instrumentation, so final stats are never published. Consistent with that, `stats/jakarta.enterprise/jakarta.enterprise.cdi-api/3.0.0/` contains only `execution-metrics.json` and no `stats.json`, so dynamic-access coverage is unavailable for the run.\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Check out the preserved branch and rerun metadata generation for `jakarta.enterprise:jakarta.enterprise.cdi-api:3.0.0` in an environment where `native-image-agent` is installed and matches `GRAALVM_HOME`.\n2. If that rerun succeeds, publish/regenerate the missing `stats.json` for `3.0.0` and confirm the candidate can be merged.\n3. If it still fails, inspect the GraalVM/native-image-agent setup used by the workflow and fix the library-path or toolchain configuration before rerunning this coordinate."}}
